comments:
(Ardit, 2012) looked at samples with obvious disordering on the sites we label Al and Nb.  In their N00 sample the occupation of our Al site is 80\% aluminum and 20\% niobium, with the reverse concentrations on our Nb site. 
 (Pederson, 1962) analyzed a sample of AlNbO$_{4}$ assuming that these sites were fully ordered. The atomic positions listed there have some errors, so we used the data found by Ardit {\em et al.} 
 The atomic positions for this structure are not found in the main text.  They are filed as \href{http://www.minsocam.org/MSA/AmMin/TOC/2012/MJ12_Data/Ardit_p910_12.zip}{item \#AM-12-035 in the American Mineralogist repository}.
